main event: Multiple unidentified objects were spotted in the sky over a location in the Pacific Ocean, passing from south to north at high speeds.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright blue-green lights, estimated to be at an altitude of 30,000 feet and traveling at speeds up to 2,000 knots.
The objects were observed passing through an area with coordinates 12-22-04N 133-44E over a period of around 3 minutes.
Additional reports were received of 6 objects on the same track, passing from left to right at an elevation of 10 degrees off the horizon, at an estimated altitude of 53,000 to 60,000 feet.
The objects were described as appearing as 'vectors' that were evenly spaced and at a lower altitude than a typical meteor.
The objects did not have tails behind them as a meteor would.
sighted object: bright blue-green lights, estimated to be at an altitude of 30,000 feet and traveling at speeds up to 2,000 knots; additional reports of 6 objects on the same track
photographs: no photographs included in the report
